dures and external regulatory requirements. Your responsibilities Accounting and Financial Transactions: Performing general accounting activities, applying techniques and standards to solve unusual issues. Applying accounting techniques and standard practices to the classification and recording of financial transactions. Reviewing accounting journals in accordance with the tables of authority. Reporting and Analysis: Executing accounting analyses and reports as assigned. Understanding United States Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (US GAAP) reporting requirements, with a detailed knowledge of International Financial Reporting Standards (IFRS) and experience in implementing new standards. Co-ordinating with the Hub to ensure all reporting is completed accurately and in a timely manner. Involving in projects, providing insight and contributing to project success by through financial data analysis and executing financial related tasks. Supporting Broad Based Black Economic Empowerment (B-BBEE) process through providing financial info as and when required. Balance sheet Reviews & reconciliations: Reviewing reconciliations by applying technical accounting skills. Following up on reconciliation queries and resolution. Preparing balance sheet review and highlight areas that need attention. Internal controls: Participating in internal control testing and prepares relevant documentation. Demonstrating a good understanding of controls over financial reporting. Risk assessment of Financials: Supporting management with assessment of balance sheet and off-balance sheet risk through regular reviews with business, following up on long outstanding matters, finding mitigating solutions. Conducting investigations and reconciliations of accounts monthly. Implementing continuous improvement. Financial Statements: Preparing of annual financial statements. Fiduciary: Liaising with external auditors during audits. Ensuring compliance with companies act of South Africa. Project Management: Managing regular projects in accounting area. Safety and Integrity: Living ABB\u2019s core values of safety and integrity, which means taking responsibility for your own. actions while caring for your colleagues and the business. Your background A bachelor\u2019s degree in accounting is mandatory. Holding a post degree in finance or CA(SA) qualification would be an added advantage. Minimum 4-5 years\u2019 experience in a similar role (general accounting or shared services) along with experience of implementing new IFRS standards. Having project management experience in the financial arena will be an added advantage. Required hands on experience in working of ERP systems like SAP. Ability to lead and manage a small team, strong interpersonal skills. Required in-depth knowledge of MS Office, specifically Excel Intermediate to advanced level. Required strong good communication and interpersonal skills. More about us Bring your very own sense of pride and purpose as you help us drive forward the Fourth Industrial Revolution \u2013 creating a sustainable future for our planet, and your career. Harness the power of our diverse global network, as you collaborate with and learn from our world-class teams. Above all, challenge yourself every day. Let\u2019s write the future, together. Should you be interested in applying for this vacancy and for any additional information please refer to the ABB Career page: https://new.abb.com/careers. Take note, that only application received via the ABB Career page will be considered. Reference Number ZA73762079_E2 Publication date 2020-06-11 Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
